Description: Disc foot and lower wall fragment of East Greek pottery thin-walled open vessel (cup?); perhaps dip-glazed outside; glazed inside; inscribed under foot.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Buried in sand under the west wall of Temenos.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 673)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.739)
